There is now a car park for the Manchester Central Convention Complex
(GMex plus the Manchester International Convention Centre) that is
contained within the vaulted basement of the old Central Station.  The
structure is not on stilts, it is formed of brick vaults.

After Manchester Central Station closed, and in the approximately ten
years before it was converted to GMex, I think the train shed was used
for car parking, but not the basement.  If I recall correctly, the
conversion of the basement into a car park only happened during the
conversion of the train shed into GMex.

